# Browser Automation

**Browser Use Cases:**
- Test Next.js pages and components
- Verify API endpoints
- Check documentation rendering
- Validate user flows

**Configuration:**
- Use browser for E2E testing scenarios
- Screenshot on errors for debugging
- Test responsive design
- Verify accessibility

**Implementation:**
- Create browser test scripts in `scripts/browser-tests/`
- Use browser automation for documentation preview
- Test Nextra documentation rendering
- Validate API responses

**Browser Testing Patterns:**
- Navigate to pages and verify content
- Test form submissions
- Verify API endpoint responses
- Check documentation rendering
- Validate responsive design
- Test accessibility features

**Best Practices:**
- Use browser for testing web functionality
- Screenshot on errors for debugging
- Test both desktop and mobile views
- Verify accessibility compliance
- Test documentation rendering

